  <explnote id="DLM2846703" in.amend="false" irdnumbering="no" rule-after="yes" rule-before="yes" pco.suffix="0003" stage="published" year="2010" raised.by="Government" sop.no="118">
    <heading>Explanatory note</heading>
    <para>
      <text>This Supplementary Order Paper amends an amendment to the Designs Act 1953 in the Regulatory Improvement Bill to clarify that the Commissioner of Designs has a discretion when making an order to restore lapsed copyright in a registered design. This is consistent with similar provisions in the Patents Bill.</text>
    </para>
  </explnote>
